# Function to add Bonferroni-corrected p-values to an existing tbl_summary object
add_corrected_pvalues_multiple <- function(tbl_summary, df, categorical_vars, group_var) {
  # Check if categorical_vars and group_var are in the data frame
  if (!all(categorical_vars %in% names(df)) | !(group_var %in% names(df))) {
    stop("Specified variables are not present in the data frame.")
  }

  # Function to perform 2x2 chi-squared test for one level of a categorical variable
  chi_squared_test <- function(df, level, categorical_var, group_var) {
    # Create 2x2 table
    table_2x2 <- table(
      df[[group_var]],
      ifelse(df[[categorical_var]] == level, level, 'Other')
    )
    
    # Perform chi-squared test
    test_result <- chisq.test(table_2x2)
    
    # Extract p-value
    p_value <- test_result$p.value
    
    return(p_value)
  }
  
  # Initialize a list to store corrected p-values data frames
  all_corrected_p_values <- list()

  # Loop through each categorical variable
  for (categorical_var in categorical_vars) {
    # Get the unique levels of the categorical variable
    levels_categorical <- unique(na.omit(df[[categorical_var]]))
    
    # Calculate individual p-values for each level of the categorical variable
    p_values <- sapply(levels_categorical, function(level) chi_squared_test(df, level, categorical_var, group_var))
    
    # Apply Bonferroni correction
    corrected_p_values <- p.adjust(p_values, method = "bonferroni")
    
    # Create a data frame with the results
    p_values_df <- data.frame(
      variable = categorical_var,
      level = levels_categorical,
      corrected_p_value = corrected_p_values,
      stringsAsFactors = FALSE
    )
    
    # Store the data frame in the list
    all_corrected_p_values[[categorical_var]] <- p_values_df
  }
  
  # Combine all p-values data frames into one
  combined_p_values_df <- bind_rows(all_corrected_p_values)

  # Add "Corrected P-Value" column to the table_body if it doesn't exist
  if (!"Corrected p-value" %in% colnames(tbl_summary$table_body)) {
    tbl_summary <- tbl_summary %>%
      modify_table_body(
        ~ .x %>%
          mutate(Corrected = NA_character_)
      )
  }

  # Update the "Corrected P-Value" column in tbl_summary$table_body
  for (categorical_var in categorical_vars) {
    indices <- which(tbl_summary$table_body$variable == categorical_var)
    for (index in indices) {
      level <- tbl_summary$table_body$label[index]
      corrected_p_value <- combined_p_values_df$corrected_p_value[
        combined_p_values_df$variable == categorical_var &
        combined_p_values_df$level == level
      ]
      if(length(corrected_p_value) > 0) {
        tbl_summary$table_body$Corrected[index] <- ifelse(corrected_p_value < 0.001, "< 0.001", formatC(corrected_p_value, format = "f", digits = 3))
      } else {
        tbl_summary$table_body$Corrected[index] <- NA
      }
    }
  }
  
  # Modify the header to display the new column
  tbl_summary <- tbl_summary %>%
    modify_header(update = list(Corrected= "**corrected p-value**")) %>%
    modify_footnote(
      update = list(Corrected ~ "Corrected p-values with Bonferroni adjustment")
    )
  # Return the modified tbl_summary
  return(tbl_summary)
}

  tbl_summary(
    by = tinnitus,
    statistic = list(
      all_continuous()  ~ "{mean}  {sd}",
      all_categorical() ~ "{n} ({p}%)"
    ),
    label = list(
      age ~ "Age",
      gender ~ "Sex",
      race ~ "Race",
      bmi ~ "Body Mass Index",
      snort.lose.breath ~ "Snorts, gasps, or stops breathing",
      hours.sleep ~ "Hours of sleep",
      sleep.disorder ~ "Sleep Disorder",
      snoring ~ "Snoring",
      excessively.sleepy ~ "Excessively sleepy during day"
    ),
    digits = list(all_continuous() ~ c(1, 0)),
    missing = "no"
  ) %>%
  add_p(
    test = list(
      all_continuous() ~ "t.test",
      all_categorical() ~ "chisq.test"
    )
  ) %>%
  bold_labels()

# multivariate logistic regression, OR, 95% CI, prediction graphs
library(sjPlot)
library(ggplot2)

# set reference to "No Tinnitus"
unweighted$tinnitus <- relevel(unweighted$tinnitus, ref = "No Tinnitus")

# univariate
# quantitative independent variable
m1 <- glm(tinnitus ~ age,
  data = unweighted,
  family = "binomial"
)
